message.content:
cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper is about the development of a new logic system based on game semantics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper introduces a new complexity measure for interactive computations and establishes the adequacy of CL12 with respect to A-amplitude, S-space, and T-time computability. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the application of CL12 to arithmetics for polynomial time and space computability. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper introduces a new logic system that can be used as a logical basis for constructive and complexity-oriented versions of Peano arithmetic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses the language of CL12, which augments that of classical logic with the so-called choice sorts of quantifiers and connectives.
